The Orchestra is a 2D narrative driven game where the player auditions for their spot in an Orchestra. In this game you are able to meet characters 
representative of different parts of the world and a bit of their stories. This project explores themes of naturalization in the United States and the non linear, 
almost unfair process many immigrants go through to prove themselves to gain their citizenship. It was inspired by my father and our experiences as a family as we 
navigate this time in his life for the first steps of naturalization. I made this project to encourage others to be kind to those around them. With the political polarization
of the US in recent times, I have noticed how much more common it is to lead with hate and judgement. It is increasingly normalized for you to be hated by strangers
by the way you look, speak, walk, and more than ever under this government. So I wanted to create a final piece that draws you in and connects you with different characters
before knowing what the game is truly about. This way you play without any immediate prejudices in mind that you may hold. At the end, the theme is revealed to the player,
and a final statement encouraging them to be kind to others is promoted. This project was fun for me to do as I was able to work on a couple of sound pieces for the final
version as well as create the concepts for my characters which changed dramatically over time. I have recently been more interested in sound design, so I was glad to get
the opportunity to make my own music for such a personal project.

